   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>phalgun, I see you asked how to add a project.

Here's what you do:

* Log into your personal instance

* View your personal user page

* Click "Add/edit projects" in the top right

* Add a project to your personal profile, and save your personal profile

Now, you will be able go from your profile to that project's page.

Let me know if that gives you enough to go on, in order to test your
changes!

Two other hopefully useful pieces of advice:

1. You can often get help with these sorts of questions on #openhatch , the
IRC channel

If you're unsure how to join, by all means ask me here! You can find some
information on it in our technical documentation at
<a href="http://openhatch.readthedocs.org/">http://openhatch.readthedocs.org/</a>

2. You can create Django models via the command line

You may be familiar with 'python manage.py runserver', which is how to run
the web app on your own computer. You can also do

python manage.py shell_plus

and this gives you a Python shell that you can use to interact with the
oh-mainline codebase and database. For example, at that prompt, you can run:

&gt;&gt;&gt; Project.create_dummy(name='My Project')

and that will create a Project object.

You can see the implementation of create_dummy() in mysite/search/models.py

One more thing -- I realize it has been ages since you asked your very
reasonable questions on this ticket! Apologies that it took us so long to
answer you well. I'd love to hear from you -- are you still interested in
working on this? We'd love it if so!

If not, then tell us too, and we'll understand.

Best,

Asheesh.</pre>
   </td>
